# =========================================================================
# DEVELOPER DOCUMENTATION & NEXT STEPS
# =========================================================================
# Environment configuration files (.env, .env.local) are ignored in Git
# to prevent checking in local database secrets or API tokens.
#
# Quickstart Guide:
#
# 1. Database Setup:
#    - MySQL server must be active on port 3306.
#    - Default testing credential password: Root@123
#    - The database (store_rating_platform) is created automatically by the backend.
#
# 2. Run Backend (Port 5000):
#    - Navigate to '/backend' directory.
#    - Ensure you have a '.env' file configured.
#    - Run: npm install
#    - Run: npm run dev
#
# 3. Run Frontend (Port 5173):
#    - Navigate to '/frontend' directory.
#    - Run: npm install
#    - Run: npm run dev
# =========================================================================
